      "position": 4,
      "content": "EXAM CREDIT",
      "contentHtml": null
    },
    {
      "id": "d7996f45-6887-ef11-8474-000d3a37e3b6",
      "type": "GeneralText",
      "area": "General",
      "position": 5,
      "content": "Some Advanced Placement (AP), International Baccalaureate Higher Level (IBH), and Advanced Level (A-level) exams satisfy UCSC course requirements. UCSC's exam credit policies may be found on the Degree Progress Unit website .",
      "contentHtml": "<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Some Advanced Placement (AP), International Baccalaureate Higher Level&nbsp;(IBH), and Advanced Level (A-level) exams satisfy UCSC course requirements. UCSC's exam credit policies may be found on the </span><a href=\"https://degreeprogress.ucsc.edu/transfer-exam-credit/exam-credit/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Degree Progress Unit website</a><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">.</span></p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "a09a6f45-6887-ef11-8474-000d3a37e3b6",
      "type": "GeneralTitle",
      "area": "General",
      "position": 6,
      "content": "Creative Technologies B.A.",
      "contentHtml": null
    },
    {
      "id": "a29a6f45-6887-ef11-8474-000d3a37e3b6",
      "type": "GeneralText",
      "area": "General",
      "position": 7,
      "content": "The Creative Technologies (CT) program at UC Santa Cruz welcomes transfer students. Prior to transferring, we recommend that prospective transfer students complete at least one lower-division course from each of the following categories: One introductory arts course in theory or history One practice-based, \"maker\"/production-oriented arts course In the \"Recommended Preparation\" section below, you will find lists of courses approved to fulfill the CT major declaration coursework requirement. Transfer students who have completed courses they believe match either of the two categories listed above, but that are not listed in the \"Recommended Preparation\" section below, may petition to have these courses counted towards their CT major declaration requirements. Students will have an opportunity to consult with the CT advisor about their prior arts coursework before enrolling in their first quarter. Minimum Unit Requirement Articulated courses listed in the \"Recommended Preparation\" section below that are less than 3 units may fulfill the CT major declaration coursework requirement in either category when 3 or more semester units are accrued. Students may combine different courses from the same category to reach the 3 semester unit minimum. Students are also encouraged to complete the California General Education Transfer Curriculum (Cal-GETC) or all UC Santa Cruz general education requirements before transferring. For guidance on incorporating Cal-GETC into your academic plan, consult your community college counselor. Please visit the Creative Technologies website to learn more about this major. UC Santa Cruz General Catalog: Creative Technologies B.A. Program Statement For more information and advising on the creative technologies major, please contact the undergraduate advisor at creative@ucsc.edu .",
      "contentHtml": "<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">The Creative Technologies (CT) program at UC Santa Cruz welcomes transfer students. Prior to transferring, we recommend that prospective transfer students complete at least one lower-division course from each of the following categories:</span></p><p><br></p><ol><li><strong style=\"font-size: 14px;\">One introductory arts course in theory or history</strong></li><li><strong style=\"font-size: 14px;\">One practice-based, \"maker\"/production-oriented arts course</strong></li></ol><p><br></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(29, 32, 36); font-size: 14px;\">In the \"Recommended Preparation\" section below, </span><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">you will find lists of courses approved to fulfill the CT major declaration coursework requirement.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Transfer students who have completed courses they believe match either of the two categories listed above, but that are not listed in the \"Recommended Preparation\" section below, may petition to have these courses counted towards their CT major declaration requirements. Students will have an opportunity to consult with the CT advisor about their prior arts coursework before enrolling in their first quarter.</span></p><p><br></p><p><strong style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><u>Minimum Unit Requirement</u></strong></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Articulated courses listed in the \"Recommended Preparation\" section </span><span style=\"font-size: 14px; color: rgb(29, 32, 36);\">below</span><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"> that are less than 3 units may fulfill the CT major declaration coursework requirement in either category when 3 or more semester units are accrued. Students may combine different courses from the same category to reach the 3 semester unit minimum.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Students are also encouraged to complete the&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://admission.universityofcalifornia.edu/admission-requirements/transfer-requirements/preparing-to-transfer/general-education-igetc/cal-getc/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>California General Education Transfer Curriculum (Cal-GETC)</strong></a><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;or all UC Santa Cruz general education requirements before transferring. For guidance on incorporating Cal-GETC into your academic plan, consult your community college counselor. </span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Please visit the </span><a href=\"https://creative.ucsc.edu/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Creative Technologies website</a><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"> to learn more about this major.</span></p><p><a href=\"https://catalog.ucsc.edu/en/current/general-catalog/academic-units/arts-division/creative-technologies/creative-technologies-ba/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"font-size: 14px;\">UC Santa Cruz General Catalog: Creative Technologies B.A. Program Statement</a></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">For more information and advising on the creative technologies major, please contact the undergraduate advisor at </span><a href=\"mailto:creative@ucsc.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"font-size: 14px;\">creative@ucsc.edu</a><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">.</span></p>"
    }
